<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/6021337-daniel"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1358736634i/6021337._UX100_CR0,12,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/6021337-daniel">Daniel</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">This is bizarre...How can anyone be so confused to need to ask others if it is acceptable for them to read a book due to the language in use of that e<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">This is bizarre...How can anyone be so confused to need to ask others if it is acceptable for them to read a book due to the language in use of that era not fitting the societal demands of today?<br /><br />Its as ridiculous as refusing classic texts, even fairytales, on the same basis that they do not meet our modern standards for inclusiveness and non gender specificity as the hallmark of acceptable. Its a hideous symptom of a society gone very wrong indeed...<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
